column5: Wow, what a great day! Awesome report! HH
Incredible day weelkend on the water!! Thanks for the report!

They go 23 for 26 on Simcoe lakers.ONE, WAS TAKEN FOR TABLE FARE.  What a great start and  finish with a doubleheader.  It was a great day to be out with my buds.On the water at 7 am,lines down by 7:20.First fish on 10 minutes later,but the rookie blew it at the boat.  It was pretty much a none stop hit til 1 pm.A bit of a lul til we hit into 21 of 23. To end the day 23 for 26,Tybo and I ,get into a double.  I had a great day.Im bugged out and burnt out.  I,ll let the vids,do the rest of the talking.   LETS DO THIS AGAIN NEXT WEEKEND FELLAS.  <object style="height: 390px; width: 640px"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pnQ69wVBkcw?version=3&feature=player_detailpage"><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pnQ69wVBkcw?version=3&feature=player_detailpage"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always"><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pnQ69wVBkcw?version=3&feature=player_detailpage" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" allowScriptAccess="always" width="640" height="360"></object>  <object style="height: 390px; width: 640px"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YI6XoYo_TvY?version=3&feature=player_detailpage"><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YI6XoYo_TvY?version=3&feature=player_detailpage"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always"><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YI6XoYo_TvY?version=3&feature=player_detailpage" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" allowScriptAccess="always" width="640" height="360"></object>  Landing. Excellent B, that's quite a bunch of fish to catch in one day, bet your arms are sore     Glad the three of you had a blast!   Paul is still power washing the gnats out of the boat.  He was covered in them when he got home and they're coming out of his carry bag and hair.  I'm not going anywhere near the boat right now

I see the bugs have gotten better since the last video .  I should be jealous (ok I am) but it's great to see friends having fun like that.  "I didn't loose him, I know exactly where he is" - classic.
Well I bet these couple days made up for a lousy winter.  Nice fishing & videos

He said Tidy Car was going to take care of that.  I,ll bet he dosent mind though,after the day we had.   THANKS AGAIN BUDDY,FOR TAKING ME AND TERRY OUT.  :good:  :good:  :good:  :good:  :good:  :good:
Good show Gents!!!!!!
You guys are having too much fun   Loved the videos Brian.   Some beauties in those vids
Dang now that's a motley crew there looks like a great day guys congrats
What a fun time that must have been. Congrats guys.
nice shooting there fellas. What a day

it was a great day thanks guys  who said there were not as many bugs bugs up my nose and between my toes tried to get in my eyes a few crawled on my thighs in my ears and in my beers pop  on my back and up my crack...bugs oh yeah    but lots of fun for sure   <iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/tXo4OKwMQUg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
That was an AWESOME vid bud. I got to learn that stuff.   Great day,and thanks.
Really awesome videos, loved them.  Oh, and Paul says there's a great Terry butt shot, this I have to see
Man oh Man !!! You guys sure know how to party  !!! This repoert was incerdible. Love the vids, and those fish are fiesty as al get-out !!!!  Thanks for sharing
Working on it.Many vids to work through.

Warning: Parental Advisory. Shake,n of the bootie may be involved.  Sorry buddy.A request,is a request. great day guys!  awe inspiring outing
Shake yer booty Terry      Holy bug ass.  Wonder if they come out in the wash or if they stay in the washing machine for the next load of laundry

You guys do realize if you put the canopy up the bugs wont come under...they will stay outside in the sun....Nice shooting ....do you guys normally use the noodle rods and spinning reels for downrigging? sure does look like fun....Good on ya ALL for a memorable outing for sure
That,s all I had Dave. I have no Idea where my rigger stuff went.The rod on the right, is one of my float rods.
What a great outing! Lotsa great footage too! How deep were you guys fishing? Thanks for the super report.  ps. This gnome gnu dat dey were gnats.
Morning Roy  125fow up to 90 fow.All fish came on the same two lures all day.
Now that is a great report!
And that gnats juice,does not come out after washing.
